org.sobotics.chatexchange.chat.event

Class EventType<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sobotics.chatexchange.chat.event.EventType<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the message for this event.

    public final class EventType<T>
extends Object
    This class represents a chat event.

    An event is an action that happened in a room and contains a message. This class is final and cannot be instantiated, only the pre-defined constants must be used.

    Author:
    Tunaki

    • Field Detail

      • MESSAGE_POSTED

        public static final EventType<MessagePostedEvent> MESSAGE_POSTED
        Event raised when a message is posted in a room. This event only targets messages posted by users, and not system-generated messages (like adding a feed).

        All messages posted by users raise this event, even replies or mentions.

      • MESSAGE_EDITED

        public static final EventType<MessageEditedEvent> MESSAGE_EDITED
        Event raised when a message is edited in a room.

        All messages posted by users and then edited raise this event, even replies or mentions.

      • MESSAGE_REPLY

        public static final EventType<MessageReplyEvent> MESSAGE_REPLY
        Event raised when a reply is posted to the current logged-in user. A reply is a message targeting a specific other message. In chat, this is the :{messageId} feature.

        When this event is raised, a corresponding MESSAGE_POSTED or MESSAGE_EDITED will be raised. This event is still useful to listen specifically to replies of one's messages instead of all posted / edited messages.

        Note that you can reply to a previous message of yourself: if the current logged-in user posts a message starting with :{messageId}, where the message with that id is one of their own, this event will be raised.

      • USER_MENTIONED

        public static final EventType<UserMentionedEvent> USER_MENTIONED
        Event raised when a mention of the current logged-in user is made. A mention is a message pinging a user without replying to a specific message. In chat, this is the @{username} feature.

        When this event is raised, a corresponding MESSAGE_POSTED or MESSAGE_EDITED will be raised. This event is still useful to listen specifically to mentions of the logged-in user instead of all posted / edited messages.

        Note that you cannot mention yourself in a message: if the current logged-in user is foo and they post a message containing @foo, this event will not be raised.

      • USER_ENTERED

        public static final EventType<UserEnteredEvent> USER_ENTERED
        Event raised when a user is entering the chat room. This event is only raised when the user wasn't previously in the room, meaning that they previously left it or never entered.

      • USER_LEFT

        public static final EventType<UserLeftEvent> USER_LEFT
        Event raised when a user is leaving the chat room, either as a result of inactivity or because they clicked the "leave" link.

      • MESSAGE_STARRED

        public static final EventType<MessageStarredEvent> MESSAGE_STARRED
        Event raised when a message is starred, unstarred, pinned or unpinned.

      • MESSAGE_DELETED

        public static final EventType<MessageDeletedEvent> MESSAGE_DELETED
        Event raised when a message is deleted.

      • KICKED

        public static final EventType<KickedEvent> KICKED
        Event raised when a user was kicked out of the chat room.
